        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(providers): release stream reader lock after classifying SDK stream body",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n**What problem does this PR solve?**\n\n- Fix classification: Defensive reader-lock release in `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody`.\n- Root cause: The finally block at line 351 calls `reader.cancel()` but not `reader.releaseLock()`. Every other stream-reader finally block in the core follows the pattern of calling both (see `http-error-body.ts:11`, `provider-http-errors.ts:44`, `voice-call/response-body.ts:28`, `nodes-camera.ts:167`).\n- Why this is pattern-match fix: This PR aligns `classifyOpenAISdkStreamBody` with 4+ other sites that already call both `cancel()` and `releaseLock()`.\n- Patch quality notes: 3 lines added. Purely defensive.\n\n**Why does this matter now?**\n\n- Consistency: This is the last stream-reader site in `src/agents/` that does not follow the dual-release pattern.\n\n**What is intentionally out of scope?**\n\n- Does NOT change: stream content sniffing logic, SSE normalization, or the `reader.cancel()` call.\n\n**What should reviewers focus on?**\n\n- Pattern consistency: Compare with `http-error-body.ts:11`, `provider-http-errors.ts:44`, `voice-call/response-body.ts:28`.",
